    CORRECTED while re-homing: `#asf/4-eli/hyp-checkpoint-forking-failure-modes` is NOT "still unwritten" (78 lines, `discussion-grade`/`draft`, verified); the κ̂ estimator is *"appears never to have been run"* in ASF's own words, not flatly never-run, and its stated confound (hold $M_{\tau^-}$ fixed across goal conditions) is a design constraint on us; the RNG bullet cited archived ORIENTATION — the world layer IS keyed/stateless now (`noise.rs`) while `vivarium-core`'s stepped stream and the per-agent splittable-seed decision are untouched, so the prerequisite stands; the open research question cited a `CLAUDE.md` that no longer carries it — `doc/design/DESIGN.md` does, and §2 points there (see `the-bet-does-not-rest-on-one-question`, which corrects what this entry first claimed); phase numbers per `scribal-and-a-1-indexed-ladder`; `\|…\|` → `\lVert…\rVert` per FORMAT §6. All 19 slugs verified to resolve; `bin/lint-md` clean.
    ⚠ **THE SECTION NUMBERS ARE IDENTIFIERS AND MUST NOT BE RENUMBERED.** `DECISIONS` (this file), `doc/plan/vivium-operational-workflow.md`, `doc/plan/regula-conformance-design.md`, and `nomotheke.rs` cite `ASF.md §2` / `§7.1` / `§7.5` by number, and the file has no slug scheme. §0's removal therefore left §§1–7 in place rather than closing the gap; the five `ASF.md §0` pointers were repointed to `ETHICS.md` (ordinum, both plan docs, taxonomy-spike ×2). A slug scheme for this file's sections is the real fix and is not done.
