|decision[the-bet-does-not-rest-on-one-question] :date 2026-07-16 :by joseph :status decided :topic process
  :session 016WWpYtpHx9fAMdyehRxpSX
  The framing **"the open question the whole bet rests on (do not assume it away)"** is REMOVED, and with it every ranking attached to the identifiability question: *"the first thing worth testing when we get there"*, *"THE interesting research question"*, *"vivarium's ONE open research question"*. The QUESTION survives, tagged as the guess it is. The claims about its rank do not.
  |reason  Joseph, 2026-07-16: **"This is exactly the kind of unfounded assertions presented authoritatively all over vivarium that was the crucial reason for me archiving everything"** — and, of `DESIGN.md`'s own surviving header, *"same confident garbage."* The assertion is almost certainly false, and was authored by an agent that had read a tiny fraction of vivarium and of ASF. FORMAT §6 already forbids the shape — *an absolute is a claim with no predicate* — and already prescribes the remedy: **the fix is precision, not silence.** So the question stays and the ranking goes; what is left is checkable.
  |impact
    ⚠ **RE-PROMOTION OUT OF `.archive/` IS HOW IT GOT BACK IN.** The overclaim was archived 2026-07-13. On 2026-07-16 the session re-homing `ASF.md` read it out of `.archive/CLAUDE.md`, believed it, and wrote it into live canon — while citing FORMAT §5 and §6 in the same commit. That file also carries the Prime Question, the modified-equation tool, the bias-vs-noise audit and the authority-is-not-evidence guard, correct, a few lines away; `.archive/README.md` calls it *"Substantial and much of it true."* **So the overclaim was not marked by its neighbours, and the harness auto-loads these files into context, where they arrive shaped like canon.** That is what is verified, and it is about ONE file.
    **Proposed rule (claude, unratified): adjudicate the PASSAGE, not the file.** Re-homing a file whole is the move that skipped the judgment.
    ⚠⚠ **AND TWO DRAFTS OF THIS ENTRY EACH BROKE THE RULE THE ENTRY EXISTS TO ENFORCE.** Draft 1 asserted *"archived text is archived because it failed; reading it confers no authority"* — contradicting `CLAUDE.md`, `.archive/README.md`, and `disposition-of-the-2026-07-13-archive`, all three of which say the opposite and all three of which its author had read. Draft 2, written to correct draft 1, asserted the archive as a whole is **"UNSORTED"** with correct and failed material mixed, *"across a file that earns it in most places"* — a measured-sounding property of ~14 files, claimed by an author who had read two, from one file's evidence plus one sentence of Joseph's. **Joseph, 2026-07-17: "You failed the test if you wrote a superlative absolute assertion in the permanent record as if you knew everything in .archive."** Both drafts reached for a rule that removes the need to judge each passage; that is the same move the overclaim itself is, and it is cheaper than reading, which is why it keeps winning. **The archive's condition is Joseph's claim, carried as his** — 2026-07-17: *"there is correct stuff in .archive — just mixed with lots of fluff and confusion."*
    Second-order: the same session reported `DESIGN.md` as carrying the question "with better epistemic precision" on the strength of its `*Guess / unverified:*` tag alone, without reading the heading two lines above it, which was the same overclaim. **A tag on a paragraph does not make its frame honest, and spotting one honest marker is not an audit.**
    NOT edited: `.archive/CLAUDE.md:55–57` — frozen archaeology, and now the specimen. The archive is exactly where it belongs.
  |ref doc/design/DESIGN.md ("An open empirical question") · ASF.md §2 · .archive/CLAUDE.md:55-57 (the specimen) · FORMAT.md §6 (No absolutes) · corrects `asf-bridge-returns-to-the-live-tree` |impact

|decision[segments-are-sole-claim-truth] :date 2026-07-20 :by joseph :status decided :topic process
  :session grok-front-door-telos
  CLAIM SEGMENTS UNDER core/src/ ARE THE SOLE SOURCE OF TRUTH FOR PROJECT CLAIMS. The slug is the identity; core/OUTLINE.md orders; FORMAT.md rules. Design prose, architecture notes, spikes, and session maps are substrate until their claims live in a segment. Fun is allowed; it must not mint unowned claims or outrank segment work this phase.
  |reason
    Joseph, 2026-07-20: the front door was smashed open (archive) without a real door built; multi-telos + empty core caused agent drift into code and rediscovery. Directive: "The slugs / the segments *shall be* the only source of truth going forward." Segment home: #scope-segment-canon.
  |impact
    CLAUDE.md and README rewritten as routers; first foundational segment batch landed under core/src/. Further work extracts claims from existing corpus into slugs; no new ORIENTATION-class state maps.
  |ref core/src/scope-segment-canon.md · core/OUTLINE.md · CLAUDE.md
